properties.areaDesc: Delaware Bay waters south of East Point NJ to Slaughter Beach DE
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 11 at 3:16AM EST until January 12 at 12:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and
rough waters expected.

* WHERE...Lower Delaware Bay including the portion south of East
Point NJ to Slaughter Beach DE.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to noon EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO NOON EST SUNDAY
